               <head>Miscellaneous literary works, 6 items</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129379">
                  <summary>Collection of multiple works on lexicography, isopsephy, literary style and prosody. Original nineteenth-century boards, detached from spine; fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85142883" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_76Ax-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="58v">ff. 1v-58v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on poetic figures and techniques attributed to a certain <persName key="person_f7414" role="att">Muḥaqqiq Ṭūsī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 58v): completed by <persName key="person_f7212" role="scr">Karīmbakhsh</persName> (written as unlinked initials: KRYMBKhSh) on 2 Jumādá al-S̲ānī 1245/29 November 1829. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21792">Miʿyār al-ashʿār</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21792">معيار الاشعار</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85142883" n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_76Ax-item2">
                     <locus from="59r" to="60r">ff. 59r-60r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Brief untitled collection of Arabic and Persian murabbaʿ poems on the theme of qavāfī, some attributed to <persName key="person_f7200" role="att">Jār Allāh ʿAllāmah</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008109072 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh86004553" n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_76Ax-item3">
                     <locus from="63v" to="108r">ff. 63v-108r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Rare treatise on the science of letters, their lexicographical and normative importance in the Persian language. </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                        <p>Transcribed in a neater nastaʿlīq hand than other tracts earlier in the same volume. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_58752912"> Bahār, Lālah Tīk Chand</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_58752912">بهار، لاله تيک چند</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21793">Javāhir al-ḥurūf</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21793">جواهر الحروف</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010106696 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563" n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_76Ax-item4">
                     <locus from="111v" to="138v">ff. 111v-138v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Unidentified treatise commenting on the ghazals of the poet <persName key="person_56731778" role="ant">Ḥāfiẓ Shīrāzī</persName>, endorsed on the first page (f. 111r) as <title>Sharḥ-i baʿz̤ī ashʿār-i Khvājah Ḥāfiẓ-i Shīrāzī</title>, by <persName key="person_f7311" role="aut">Mīrzā Khayr Allāh the muhandis</persName> or engineer. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is without a preface or introduction, beginning with the opening line of the first ghazal addressed to the sāqī. </p>
                        <p>Not dated. </p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7311">Mīrzā Khayr Allāh the muhandis</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008109073" n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_76Ax-item5">
                     <locus from="139v" to="170r">ff. 139v-170r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on rhyme and prosody, endorsed on the first page (f. 139r) as <title>Vāfiyah fī fann al-ʿurūz̤ va al-qāfiyah</title>, which differs from the title stated in the author’s khātimah (f. 170r). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated </p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21794">Zubdat al-bayān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21794">زبدة البيان</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_118422342">Mīr Shams al-Dīn "Faqīr"</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_118422342">مير شمس الدّين فقير</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008109073" n="6" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_76Ax-item6">
                     <locus from="170v" to="184v">ff. 170v-184v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on innovative conceits in poetry or fann-i badīʿ. </p>
                        <p>The work is a mukhtaṣar based on the <title>Miftāḥ</title> of <persName key="person_61532835" role="ant">Kakkākī</persName> and <title>Mutavval</title> of <persName key="person_641145857886423020766" role="ant">Taftāzānī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work consists of a dībāchah, muqaddimah, two faṣl, and a khātimah. </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 184v): completed Tuesday, 5 Shavvāl 1245/30 March 1830. </p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21795">Khulāṣat al-badīʿ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21795">خلاصة البديع</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_118422342">Mīr Shams al-Dīn "Faqīr"</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_118422342">مير شمس الدّين فقير</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
